    • Method Detail

      • onObjectTapped

        boolean onObjectTapped(java.util.List<ARObject> objects)
        A callback indicating that at least one ARObject is located at the users tap point.

        If there are ARObjects located at the users tap point, this callback will be made before ARController.OnTapListener.onTap(PointF). If true is returned from this callback, onTap(PointF) on the tap listener will not be called.

        Parameters:
        objects - A list of selected ARObject objects
        Returns:
        true if consumed (which prevents calling of ARController.OnTapListener.onTap(PointF)), false otherwise.
